article.description: Landon Taliaferro had 24 points as Fairfield topped Manhattan 68-60 on Friday night.
article.headline: Taliaferro leads Fairfield past Manhattan 68-60
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. -- Landon Taliaferro had 24 points as Fairfield topped Manhattan 68-60 on Friday night. Aidas Kavaliauskas had 12 points and six assists for Fairfield (6-9, 2-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), which snapped its four-game home losing streak. After Fairfield outscored Manhattan 40-32 in the first half, both teams scored 28 in the second as the hosts clinched the victory. The Stags' 40 points in the first half were a season high for the team. Warren Williams had 19 points for the Jaspers (6-6, 2-1). Christian Hinckson added 13 points. Fairfield faces St. Peter's at home on Wednesday. Manhattan plays Siena at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
